{
  "text": "Here \u03d5 = \u03d5(z) is an arbitrary holomorphic function with values in the the Lie algebra of G C , and the gauge transformation parameter g = g(z,z, y) is an arbitrary function with values in G C . Away from the locus z = 0, the Nahm-pole boundary condition (1.5) corresponding to a principal embedding requires \u03d5 to lie in the 'regular nilpotent orbit'. (See e.g [CITATION_1] ). At z = 0, \u03d5 must then lie in the closure of the regular nilpotent orbit, but it may define a more special nilpotent conjugacy class. To describe the possibilities, we choose a Cartan torus T with Lie algebra t in G and a principal embedding of SO(3) in G with standard generators",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "122298729"
  },
